[1] Liberia: Antiviral treatment
Date: Sat 17 Jan 2015
Source: Cherwell.org [edited]
http://www.cherwell.org/news/oxford/2015/01/16/ebola-treatment-begins-trials-in-liberia


An Oxford University team of researchers has begun a trial of a potential treatment for Ebola infection. The team is investigating brincidofovir, developed by private American healthcare company Chimerix. The trial, run by volunteers from Doctors Without Borders [MSF] and the University of Oxford, and funded by the Wellcome Trust, will test the effectiveness of the drug by comparing the fatality rate of 140 patients in Monrovia with previous Ebola fatality rates in the hospitalized Ebola patients in Monrovia, Liberia.

The 1st Ebola patient received the study drug on 2 Jan 2015. If this ongoing trial is considered successful, there will be a 2nd, larger trial in one of the 3 countries most affected by the epidemic, Guinea, Liberia, or Sierra Leone. If that also has positive results, brincidofovir will be released on a wider scale. ... - more

[Byline: Jack Doyle]

