[3] Mali: Ebola-free
Date: Sun 18 Jan 2015
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/01/18/uk-health-ebola-mali-idUKKBN0KR0XM20150118


Mali's health minister declared the West African nation free of Ebola on Sun [18 Jan 2015] following a 42-day period without a new case of the deadly virus. Mali recorded 6 deaths from Ebola. Mali's last infected patient recovered and left hospital early last month [December 2014]. At one point health officials had been monitoring more than 300 contact cases.

Mali became the 6th West African country to record a case of Ebola when a 2-year-old girl from Guinea died in October 2014. It was close to being declared Ebola free in November [2014] before a 2nd wave of infections.

